    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-09T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-09T12:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/4–946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent   <gloss target="#t_Niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-09T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 9, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 9—1:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1692. For the Secretary. Following is translation of a second note (my 1649,
                    April 7)<note n="69" xml:id="d38fn69">Not printed.</note> delivered at same time
                    as French reply on meeting of Council of Foreign Ministers transmitted in my
                    immediately preceding telegram: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Mr. Ambassador: I have informed Your Excellency that the French Govt
                            accepted the proposal of the Secretary of State regarding the meeting of
                            the Council of Foreign Ministers on April 25 at Paris.</p>
                        <p>The French Govt trusts (compte) that this meeting of the Council of
                            Foreign Ministers will be the occasion to examine German questions to
                            which the French Govt had already drawn attention of the United States
                            Govt by its communication of the first of March last reaffirming the
                            terms of its memorandum of September 13.<note n="70" xml:id="d38fn70"
                                >Reference is to the memorandum by the French Delegation to the
                                Council of Foreign Ministers, entitled “Control and Administration
                                of Germany” and designated <gloss target="#t_CFM1">C.F.M.</gloss>
                                (45) 17, September 13, 1945, <ref target="frus1945v02#pg_177">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1945, vol. <hi
                                        rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 177</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Please accept, Mr. Ambassador, et cetera. Signed: Bidault.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
